result.name: Shanghai Lao Lao

reviews.text: Food is good and served quick. Clean & pleasant deco. And pricing can be classified as cheap in Causeway Bay. Just one thing to pick on - almost no space between tables.
Good location. Noodle is delicious and famous. No similar Shanghai style restaurants can be found around the area. Idea place to have a noodle meal.
Nice restaurant, must try its xiaolongbao. They also offer seasonal new dishes

Tasty fresh noodles with variety of soups and extras. Very good quality for the budget. The service was quick and serves free tea with refills. A dinner for four came up less than 500 HKD, including a small desert. 
The restaurant is on a first floor of a building opposite to H&M.

The food isn't bad at all. If you are asking if the xiao long baos are authentic ? The answer is no. The wrapping is a by too thick for my liking and the taste is mediocre. The other dishes are quite flavourful though. A bit expensive overall to dine in.

reviews.text: 交通方便，人流繁多，大部份的食物水準都不錯，但一客$48.-的豆沙窩餅卻不怎麼樣！有點失望。
這間上海姥姥酒家，食物很好吃，價錢公道抵食
擔擔麵差過上海婆婆，又冇冷盤拼盤，令人失望！
服務員招呼殷勤,但食物水準不太高
上海菜,麵食,製作有水準,價钱算合理

reviews.text: Decent lunch place within the $50 - $70 range. Rice and noodles available, and the typical taiwanese drinks.
第二次來，點了個冬菇素菜麵。我是吃素的，所以間中會跟葷食的男友來，讓他也能吃點肉。這家餐廳的聽員要注意一下，素麵裹出現了二塊肉片，我吃了一半差點沒吐🤕😩。看來下次我還是選擇其他餐廳了。
不錯的地方，經濟抵食好味。
